# No silent scalar coercion of a WRITE map key. The map is int-keyed; `m[2.5] = 1` used
# a float key, which the write path (bare nt_check, identity-only) let through while the
# read path already base-checks. tychoc rejects; tychoc0 silently coerced the key. Both
# compilers must reject. (UB-6 completion at the map-key write position.)
fn main():
    m : [int: int] = []
    m[2.5] = 1
    println(str(len(m)))
